      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:30:1",
      "text": [
        " مَا كَانَ شَيْ‏ءٌ أَحَبَّ إِلَى رَسُولِ اللَّهِ (صلى الله عليه وآله) مِنْ أَنْ يَظَلَّ جَائِعاً خَائِفاً فِي اللَّهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473214\">H 14547</a> – Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Saalim, and others, the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘There was nothing more beloved to the Rasool<sup>saww</sup> Allah<sup>azwj</sup> than remaining hungry and fearful for the sake of Allah<sup>azwj</sup>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "99. Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Saalim, and others, the following: Abu Abdullah (a.s.) having said: ‘There was nothing more beloved to the Rasool (saww) Allah (azwj) than remaining hungry and fearful for the sake of Allah (azwj)’."
        ]
      }
